 Oregon lawmaker proposed legislation creating uniform standards for hand dryers in public restrooms .
The bill says that the recent proliferation of powerful dryers is efficient , but can trigger ringing of the ears , or cause discomfort for people with development or sensory disabilities .
It would require all new or replacement dryers to operate at a noise level no louder than 84 decibels .
It also would also ` requires downward hand dryer to blow air faster than 115 mph .